<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-07-17T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-07-17T16:00:00-05:00" n="871" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d871">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.1928/400: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Panama</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-07-17T16:00:00-05:00">July 17, 1935—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 7:49 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>89. Your 31, July 16, 2 p.m.<note n="11" xml:id="d871fn11">Not
                                printed.</note> Minister for Foreign Affairs informs me that
                            Panamanian delegation has not been further instructed in regard to the
                            proposed treaties because of the disturbed situation here which the
                            Legation has reported to the Department.</p>
                        <p>In view of the preoccupation of President Arias and the Cabinet crisis he
                            may not be able to receive me until the 19th.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>